challengeName: Mnemosyne AngularJS Web App - Duplicate Calls
detailedRequirements:
We've been building a mobile magazine application over these past few months. It grabs content from all over the internet, aggregates it together, and displays it in a nice HTML5 front end.

When testing in chrome and visiting the Home (Dashbaord) page, we found it triggerred many calls and some are duplicate, like 

 

we'd like to you to analyze and fix it.

1. identify the root cause of duplicate cases.

2. fix the duplicate calls.

3. provide a list of unique calls.

Resources

You can get the latest code from our Github repo. If you do not have access, post the forums and we will get you in. The latest version of the REST API and aggregator code are also there, if you want to setup your own environment.

a copy of the latest source code will also be attached in forum.

To ease your life of deployment, you can try drop the app code in your web server, it will use our backend services in our demo server (54.87.113.189).

How to Test

Please test the app in iPad (Potrait and landscape mode) and iPhone (Potrait mode).
